  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Courtney Fantinato",
      "poster_handle": "courtneyfantinato"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:31:18",
    "text": "That doesn't import the font file into the email, though. You need to add the font itself before applying it to the font-family."
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Jordan Ryken",
      "poster_handle": "jordan.ryken"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:31:20",
    "text": "this example is a marketing email template"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Jordan Ryken",
      "poster_handle": "jordan.ryken"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:31:38",
    "text": "that's all I had to do <@UKGV272KS> as it's a web font"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Courtney Fantinato",
      "poster_handle": "courtneyfantinato"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:33:27",
    "text": "A web font still needs to be embedded, typically in the `&lt;head&gt;` of the email. <https://www.litmus.com/blog/the-ultimate-guide-to-web-fonts>"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Courtney Fantinato",
      "poster_handle": "courtneyfantinato"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:34:10",
    "text": "Embedding is done through `@import`, `@font-face` , or `&lt;link&gt;`."
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Jillian McGuire",
      "poster_handle": "jmcguire"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:37:54",
    "text": "If I wanted to embed using those things, where would I go to do that? I know I have to go to Marketing -&gt; Files and templates -&gt; Design Tools, but then what do I click?"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Courtney Fantinato",
      "poster_handle": "courtneyfantinato"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:39:02",
    "text": "It requires a custom coded email/template."
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Jillian McGuire",
      "poster_handle": "jmcguire"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:39:51",
    "text": "Would you say my best bet is to hire a developer?"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Jillian McGuire",
      "poster_handle": "jmcguire"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:40:04",
    "text": "I need our marketing emails to be on brand"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Courtney Fantinato",
      "poster_handle": "courtneyfantinato"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:43:58",
    "text": "Yes, if that's a requirement then I would recommend an email developer. Note though that web fonts aren't supported in all email clients, so even when implemented, many will show a fallback web-safe font."
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Jillian McGuire",
      "poster_handle": "jmcguire"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 14:44:38",
    "text": "Thank you, Courtney!"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Jillian McGuire",
      "poster_handle": "jmcguire"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 19:42:56",
