      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Courtney Fantinato",
      "poster_handle": "courtneyfantinato"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 20:29:46",
    "text": "That method didn’t work for me :woman-shrugging::skin-tone-2: "
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Kyle McKay",
      "poster_handle": "kyle.p.mckay"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 20:29:51",
    "text": "Please upvote this idea!\n\n:sprocket: *<https://community.HubSpot.com/t5/HubSpot-Ideas/Allow-custom-fonts-in-drag-and-drop-editor/idi-p/746480|Allow custom fonts in drag-and-drop editor>*"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Kyle McKay",
      "poster_handle": "kyle.p.mckay"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 20:32:22",
    "edited": {
      "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 20:40:06"
    },
    "text": "Sure you can specify a google font in your drag-and-drop email template css, but it won't render for the recipient unless they have that font installed on their machine.\n\nyou need the font loaded in the email's `&lt;head&gt;`  as per <@UKGV272KS>’s point above (which the drag-and-drop editor does not provide access to)"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Kyle McKay",
      "poster_handle": "kyle.p.mckay"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 20:32:36",
    "text": "this is a big drawback of using the drag-and-drop editor in HubSpot IMO"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Kyle McKay",
      "poster_handle": "kyle.p.mckay"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 20:41:25",
    "text": "we need the HubSpot product team to either provide us access to the `&lt;head&gt;` or to build a feature that allows us to specify custom fonts in a drag-and-drop email"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Kyle McKay",
      "poster_handle": "kyle.p.mckay"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 20:45:09",
    "text": "curious to hear the resolution here.\n\ndoes HubSpot automatically strip carriage returns in rich text properties when inserted as personalization tokens?!?!"
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Steven Hambleton",
      "poster_handle": "steven994"
    },
    "time_stamp": "2023-08-28 21:09:51",
    "text": "Drag and drop custom module coding is coming at some point. In the mean time, I’ve built out several custom coded emails for HubSpot (Design Manager) with the ability to define the modules and their order."
  },
  {
    "poster": {
      "poster_name": "Steven Hambleton",
      "poster_handle": "steven994"
